C++17 + POCO + nginx + redis Project

Recommended Stack
    C++17
    POCO
    NGINX
    Redis

Use this combo:
    C++17
    POCO (HTTP Server + Client)
    Redis (cache, rate limit)
    nlohmann/json (config + payload)
    spdlog (logging)
    OpenSSL (HTTPS)

Example Architecture
    Client(browser/app) → NGINX → C++ API Gateway → Backend Services
                                        ↓
                                Auth (JWT)
                                Rate Limit (Redis)
                                Cache (Redis)
                                Routing (Config)

Design Patterns to Use
    Proxy Pattern → Forward requests
    Strategy Pattern → Load balancing
    Chain of Responsibility → Middleware (auth → logging → routing)
    Singleton → Config manager
    Factory → Route handlers

Two Architectures (Important)

    Option A: Pure C++ Gateway (Learning / Control)
        Client(browser/app) → C++ API Gateway → Backend

    Option B: Hybrid (REAL WORLD )
        Client(browser/app) → NGINX → C++ API Gateway → Backend

Easy Analogy
    Think of it like food delivery:
        Client → You (ordering food)
        NGINX → Reception
        Gateway → Manager
        Backend services → Kitchen
        Redis → Fast memory (repeat orders)